<table width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" role=
=3D"presentation" style=3D"mso-table-lspace:0pt;mso-table-rspace:0pt;word-b=
reak:break-word;"><tbody><tr><td class=3D"r" style=3D"padding-bottom:32px;"=
><div style=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;Inter&#39;,&#39=
;Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;line-height:1=
50%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margi=
n-bottom:0px;"><strong>I think one of two things need to happen here to add=
ress the threat:
Either legacy institutions like NBC News need to come up with a </strong><s=
trong><em>really</em></strong><strong> robust strategy for a post-linear fu=
ture, or one of these new influencers is going to have to take on Walter Cr=
onkite=E2=80=93level trustworthiness with the American people. I think that=
=E2=80=99s very uncertain territory ahead.</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0=
;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">For=
 sure. Not only do you need individuals who can amass that kind of
trust and credibility, but what=E2=80=99s lost is that there=E2=80=99s an i=
nfrastructure that=E2=80=99s necessary in order to do this <em>well</em>, i=
f you=E2=80=99re trying to capture the most accurate available picture of t=
he truth at any given time. And let=E2=80=99s be clear, journalism is an im=
perfect practice. Part of the crisis in trust is that for a long time, some=
 of these institutions were not forthcoming enough about how imperfect this=
 all was. You have a lot of people working very hard to get it right, but t=
hat does not
mean that they always get it right. But the infrastructure that a large org=
anization like NBC News or CNN has=E2=80=94the standards and practices depa=
rtment, the career ladder, the ability to start as a P.A. and then graduall=
y climb the chain, so that by the time you=E2=80=99re making decisions, you=
=E2=80=99ve got five, six, 10 years of experience under your belt=E2=80=94t=
hose things are critical.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">You can=E2=80=99t just walk=
 out into the world
with a phone and an Instagram account and expect to do responsible journali=
sm consistently over time. You can get it right occasionally, but these sys=
tems weren=E2=80=99t built <em>just</em> for the sake of wasting big corpor=
ations=E2=80=99 money. They were built because they were deemed to be neces=
sary for good reason to make sure that mistakes weren=E2=80=99t made very o=
ften. One of the sad pieces of the decline of these legacy institutions is =
they=E2=80=99re replaced by folks who may not have the same philosophical
commitment to pursuing the truth, but also not the resources to do it in a =
way that doesn=E2=80=99t result in a lot of mistakes and inaccuracies.</p><=
p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;marg=
in-bottom:0px;"><strong>So you don=E2=80=99t subscribe to the Elon Musk the=
sis, =E2=80=9CYou are the media.=E2=80=9D</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;=
margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">To u=
se another metaphor=E2=80=94like the drug problem, it=E2=80=99s a supply-an=
d-demand problem. There is a
supply problem in that we have a lot of bad actors out there who are floodi=
ng the zone with intentional falsehoods in pursuit of a malicious agenda. W=
e also have people with ideological agendas who may not be as overtly disho=
nest, but pick and choose their facts to construct a picture that=E2=80=99s=
 useful to their ideological agenda. You=E2=80=99ve got a lot of people con=
tributing to this problem on the supply side.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><br=
/>On the demand side, the audience is choosing to consume this. And
at a certain point, so long as individual consumers click on this stuff and=
 watch this stuff instead of the more staid middle-of-the-road brands, it=
=E2=80=99s on us, because we <em>do</em> have a choice. We can subscribe to=
 responsible news outlets; we can choose to get our news from reputable sou=
rces. But a lot of people at scale would rather scroll through TikTok and d=
o it that way. And I don=E2=80=99t know how you address that issue.</p></di=
v>
